title Enforcement via hooks, not skill prompting
edge explains commit:62dc2561b993d28b0d93605c6ea4ac6bf74aca9c

Skills are soft nudges — agents forget (proven by dogfooding this session).
Hard enforcement needs hooks/extensions:
- pi: TypeScript extensions with tool_call/tool_result hooks (~/.pi/agent/extensions/*.ts)
- claude code: custom slash commands or hooks
- git: post-commit hook that prompts for note

The skill teaches the convention. The extension enforces it.
These are different layers. Don't try to make the skill a guardrail.
